  "texts": [
    "Education systems are under increasing pressure to remain up to date in today's era of advanced technology (Awaji, 2021).",
    "Factors such as world economies, international connections, rapid technological changes, the explosion of information, national security issues, and others, are compelling those responsible for developing educational curricula to consider new, innovative teaching approaches (Wells, 2019).",
    "Technology has become a fundamental feature of daily life and increasingly important in modern education (Glaubke, 2007; McCarrick & Li, 2007).",
    "Students are keen to implement aspects of their out-of-school technological activities, such as playing computer games, using smartphones and mp3 players, and interacting on social networking sites, in the classroom (Gutnick et al., 2011; Rideout et al., 2011).",
    "Despite advancements in educational technology, Hoyles (2018) notes a tendency in classrooms to use digital applications merely as a way of expediting traditional procedures, with digital resources often replicating paper-and-pencil tasks."
  ],
